# Quantitative Portfolio Management System

## Overview
This project is a modular quantitative finance system that simulates institutional portfolio management workflows. It covers the full pipeline from market data ingestion to strategy generation, backtesting, portfolio construction, and performance analysis.

---

## Architecture

Market Data → Feature Engineering → Strategy Signals → Backtesting Engine → Portfolio Construction → Performance Analytics

---

## Key Features

- Multi-asset data pipeline (Yahoo Finance)
- Feature engineering (returns, volatility, momentum, z-score)
- Systematic trading strategies:
  - Momentum
  - Mean Reversion
  - Trend Following
- Backtesting engine with transaction costs
- Portfolio construction (equal-weight allocation)
- Performance metrics (Sharpe ratio, drawdown, returns)
- Equity curve visualization

---

## Tech Stack

- Python
- Pandas, NumPy
- Matplotlib
- yFinance
- SciPy / Statsmodels

---

## Example Outputs

- Portfolio equity curve
- Strategy performance comparison
- Risk and return metrics
- Multi-asset backtest results

---

## Future Improvements

- Risk Parity portfolio allocation
- Mean-Variance Optimization (Markowitz)
- Value at Risk (VaR) / CVaR
- Interactive dashboard (Plotly / Streamlit)
- Factor models (Fama-French)
- ML-based alpha signals

---

